<task id="050" project="ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>SpaarkeAi Code Page тАФ Extend `launch-resolver.ts` with `ChatLaunchContext` URL-param parsing</title>
    <phase>Phase 5: Surfaces + Templates</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>013</dependencies>
    <blocks>051</blocks>
    <tags>typescript, frontend, fluent-ui, react</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>TypeScript code modification of an existing critical-path module (`launch-resolver.ts`) that all entity-form ribbon launchers depend on; creates a new contract type (`ChatLaunchContext`) consumed by Action Engine invocation paths; tags include typescript + frontend</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Blocks task 051 (ribbon launchers wire to the parsed context); single critical-path task within the Phase 5 Surfaces sub-group.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/utils/launch-resolver.ts` to parse a full `ChatLaunchContext` from URL parameters when SpaarkeAi loads, and create the new contract type at `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/ChatLaunchContext.ts`. `ChatLaunchContext` is the canonical handoff payload that ribbon launchers (task 051) populate and the Spaarke AI Assistant (default playbook per task 052) consumes to scope its session тАФ entity ids, entity type, optional pre-selected Action template id, surface hint (sidePane / modal / fullPage), and optional invocation hint (e.g., "Summarize this matter"). This task ADDS a parsing function + the new type without breaking the existing `SpaarkeAiLaunchParams` contract.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior TypeScript / React engineer with deep familiarity with the Spaarke `SpaarkeAi` Code Page shell (Vite + React 19, ADR-026), Fluent UI v9 conventions (ADR-021 dark-mode parity), and Spaarke Auth v2 (`useAuth()` / `authenticatedFetch` per ADR-028). You preserve backward compatibility of the existing `SpaarkeAiLaunchParams` contract while extending it for Action Engine.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three concrete outcomes:
    1. **`ChatLaunchContext` type** тАФ a new TypeScript interface at `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/ChatLaunchContext.ts` carrying the canonical Action Engine invocation handoff fields: `entityLogicalName?`, `entityId?`, `matterId?` (alias), `actionTemplateId?` (optional pre-selected Template), `surfaceHint?` (`'sidePane' | 'modal' | 'fullPage'`), `invocationHint?` (free-text prompt to seed the chat input).
    2. **Parsing function** тАФ extend `launch-resolver.ts` with `parseChatLaunchContext(search: string): ChatLaunchContext`, which reads `window.location.search` (or an injected string for testability) and returns a populated `ChatLaunchContext`. MUST strip GUID braces (same convention as `buildLaunchUrl`). MUST tolerate missing params (every field optional). MUST NOT throw on unknown params.
    3. **Backward compatibility** тАФ `SpaarkeAiLaunchParams` continues to work for existing ribbon callers (`EntityFormLaunch.openFromEntityForm`, `WorkspaceLaunch`). `ChatLaunchContext` extends, does not replace.

    Deliverable: `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/ChatLaunchContext.ts` (new), `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/utils/launch-resolver.ts` (edited тАФ adds `parseChatLaunchContext` + extends `buildLaunchUrl` to accept the new fields), unit tests at `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/utils/__tests__/launch-resolver.test.ts`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Spec.md FR-13 mandates SpaarkeAi as the no-context default surface; FR-14 mandates ribbon launchers on Matter / Project / Account / Contact that pre-populate `ChatLaunchContext`. The existing `launch-resolver.ts` already handles `entityLogicalName` + `entityId` + `matterId`; this task expands the contract for Action Engine's three invocation paths (design.md ┬з4.5.1) тАФ the LLM's session resolution depends on the full context payload.

      The new type `ChatLaunchContext` is the boundary contract between (a) ribbon launchers populating it, (b) SpaarkeAi parsing it, and (c) the default Assistant playbook (task 052) consuming it to pick the right system prompt + always-on tools. Design.md ┬з4.5.4 lists how the agent's runtime behavior changes based on launch context тАФ this type is the wire format for that handoff.

      The parsing function MUST be safe under SSR-style invocation (where `window` might not exist) тАФ accept an optional string argument so unit tests can pass URL query strings directly without DOM dependency.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/utils/launch-resolver.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/ChatLaunchContext.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/utils/__tests__/launch-resolver.test.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ribbon/EntityFormLaunch.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ribbon/WorkspaceLaunch.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/App.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/main.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 only. No new components in this task, but any types added MUST be compatible with downstream Fluent v9 consumers; do NOT import from `@fluentui/react` (v8).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-026">Vite + singlefile + React 19 build target. New types live in `src/types/`; new utils live in `src/utils/`. Bundle stays singlefile.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Spaarke Auth v2. This task does NOT call BFF (no auth needed here), but the `ChatLaunchContext` payload MUST NOT carry tokens, access tokens, or other secret material тАФ only routing/contextual data. Verified by code review.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Backward compatibility: `SpaarkeAiLaunchParams` continues to exist; `buildLaunchUrl` accepts both shapes via union or extension. Existing ribbon callers (`EntityFormLaunch`, `WorkspaceLaunch`) MUST keep working without modification.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Parsing MUST tolerate unknown URL params (forward-compatibility with future Action Engine fields) without throwing.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No new npm dependencies. Use built-in `URLSearchParams`.</constraint>
  </constraints>

