  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, branch is `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, dependencies (task 013) marked тЬЕ in `TASK-INDEX.md`. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Read all files in `&lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;` тАФ especially design.md ┬з4.5.1 (three invocation paths), ┬з4.5.4 (surface-context awareness), and the existing `launch-resolver.ts`.</step>
    <step order="2">Create `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/ChatLaunchContext.ts` exporting the `ChatLaunchContext` interface. Document each field with TSDoc citing the source design section. Include `surfaceHint` enum-type and `invocationHint` free-text contract.</step>
    <step order="3">Edit `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/utils/launch-resolver.ts`: add `parseChatLaunchContext(search?: string): ChatLaunchContext`. Use `URLSearchParams`. Strip GUID braces on `entityId`, `matterId`, and (if a GUID) `actionTemplateId`. Tolerate missing `search` arg by reading `window.location.search` with a safe fallback for non-browser contexts.</step>
    <step order="4">Extend `buildLaunchUrl` to accept the new fields (`actionTemplateId`, `surfaceHint`, `invocationHint`) as optional inputs WITHOUT breaking the existing `SpaarkeAiLaunchParams` callers. Either widen the param type or accept a `ChatLaunchContext` union тАФ preserve the function's existing signature for backward compatibility.</step>
    <step order="5">Create unit tests at `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/utils/__tests__/launch-resolver.test.ts`: (a) `parseChatLaunchContext` with empty string returns empty object; (b) with full context returns all 6 fields; (c) GUID braces stripped on `entityId` and `actionTemplateId`; (d) unknown params tolerated (no throw); (e) `buildLaunchUrl` round-trips through `parseChatLaunchContext` (build then parse yields the same payload); (f) existing `SpaarkeAiLaunchParams` callers still work (regression).</step>
    <step order="6">Run `npm test --workspace=src/solutions/SpaarkeAi` (or the local equivalent) тАФ all tests pass. Run `npm run build:prod --workspace=src/solutions/SpaarkeAi` тАФ build succeeds with no new errors. (Use `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` if a fresh install is needed per CLAUDE.md ┬з11.)</step>
    <step order="7">Sanity-check: open `App.tsx` and confirm the existing entry path still compiles. Do NOT integrate `ChatLaunchContext` consumption into `App.tsx` in this task тАФ that integration ships with task 052 (default playbook) and is out of scope here. This task ONLY adds the type + the parser.</step>
    <step order="8">**Manual smoke test** (deferred тАФ covered by `&lt;ui-tests&gt;` section): the deep-link flow (URL with `?entityLogicalName=sprk_matter&amp;entityId=abc-123&amp;invocationHint=Summarize+this+matter`) parses correctly. This is verified by the unit test in step 5 plus the `ui-test` skill invocation at Step 9.7.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `current-task.md` with progress; checkpoint via `context-handoff` skill if &gt; 3 steps complete.</step>
    <step order="9.5">**Quality gates** (FULL rigor): run `code-review` on `launch-resolver.ts` + `ChatLaunchContext.ts`; run `adr-check` (verify ADR-021, ADR-026, ADR-028 compliance тАФ no Fluent v8 imports, singlefile bundle preserved, no token fields in `ChatLaunchContext`).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 050 status тЬЕ. Update `current-task.md`: task 050 complete; unblocks task 051.</step>
    <step order="11">If any deviations from this plan, document in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/050-deviations.md`.</step>
  </steps>

