  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/ChatLaunchContext.ts` exists and exports the `ChatLaunchContext` interface with all 6 documented optional fields (`entityLogicalName`, `entityId`, `matterId`, `actionTemplateId`, `surfaceHint`, `invocationHint`).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`parseChatLaunchContext('')` returns an empty `ChatLaunchContext` (all fields undefined) тАФ unit test passes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`parseChatLaunchContext('entityLogicalName=sprk_matter&amp;entityId={abc-123}&amp;invocationHint=Summarize+this+matter')` returns `{entityLogicalName: 'sprk_matter', entityId: 'abc-123', invocationHint: 'Summarize this matter'}` (GUID braces stripped) тАФ unit test passes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`buildLaunchUrl({entityLogicalName: 'sprk_matter', entityId: 'abc-123'})` continues to return the existing format тАФ regression test passes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`buildLaunchUrl` round-trip through `parseChatLaunchContext` yields the same payload тАФ unit test passes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Unknown URL params (e.g., `?foo=bar`) do not cause `parseChatLaunchContext` to throw тАФ unit test passes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build:prod --workspace=src/solutions/SpaarkeAi` exits 0 with no new TypeScript errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new npm dependencies added to `package.json`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`ChatLaunchContext` MUST NOT contain `accessToken`, `token`, or any secret-shaped field тАФ verified by `code-review`.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Render тАФ SpaarkeAi loads with no params">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?pagetype=webresource&amp;webresourceName=sprk_spaarkeai</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Navigate to SpaarkeAi Code Page with no query params</step>
        <step>Verify the page renders the no-context default landing (welcome panel)</step>
        <step>Open browser dev tools; check console for JavaScript errors</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Page renders without console errors; no entity context applied; `parseChatLaunchContext` returns empty object.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Deep-link flow тАФ full ChatLaunchContext from URL">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?pagetype=webresource&amp;webresourceName=sprk_spaarkeai&amp;data=entityLogicalName%3Dsprk_matter%26entityId%3Dabc-123%26invocationHint%3DSummarize%2Bthis%2Bmatter</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Navigate to SpaarkeAi Code Page with full deep-link query string</step>
        <step>Verify `parseChatLaunchContext` extracts entityLogicalName=sprk_matter, entityId=abc-123, invocationHint='Summarize this matter'</step>
        <step>Verify the context is observable in dev tools (window.__SPAARKE_LAUNCH_CONTEXT__ or React DevTools state, depending on integration plan)</step>
        <step>Check console for JavaScript errors</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>All 3 fields parsed correctly; GUID braces stripped if present; no console errors.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Dark Mode Compliance (ADR-021)">
      <steps>
        <step>Toggle dark mode in D365 user settings</step>
        <step>Reload SpaarkeAi Code Page (any URL)</step>
        <step>Verify background and text colors adapt via Fluent v9 semantic tokens (no hard-coded white or black)</step>
        <step>Verify any icons use `currentColor` for stroke/fill</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>All colors use Fluent UI v9 semantic tokens per ADR-021; no contrast failures.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    The `ChatLaunchContext` type is intentionally a superset of `SpaarkeAiLaunchParams` тАФ do not delete or rename the existing type. The existing ribbon callers in `EntityFormLaunch.ts` and `WorkspaceLaunch.ts` MUST continue to compile and behave identically.

    Task 052 (default playbook seed) will integrate `ChatLaunchContext` consumption into `App.tsx` (deciding which playbook to load based on `entityLogicalName`). That integration is out of scope here.

    Do not import `@fluentui/react` (v8) anywhere тАФ Spaarke is Fluent UI v9 only (ADR-021).

    Per spec.md FR-13: SpaarkeAi already exists; this task only EXTENDS its URL contract. Do not rewrite `App.tsx` or shell components.
  </notes>

